%% Title: ZinharCMS Tenant Isolation Flow
%% Sources: backend/src/middleware/tenant.rs; backend/src/services/rls.rs; backend/migrations/0008_v2_phase_one_organizations.sql; backend/migrations/0009_v2_phase_three_rls.sql; backend/migrations/0012_v2_phase_seven_saas_ops.sql; backend/migrations/0014_v2_phase_nine_beta_release.sql; backend/migrations/0019_v3_phase_six_installation_lifecycle.sql through backend/migrations/0024_v3_phase_ten_ratings_abuse.sql
%% Related documentation: ../multi-tenancy.md; ../relationships.md; ../database-testing.md
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Auth as Auth Middleware
    participant Tenant as Tenant Middleware
    participant Handler as Route or Service
    participant SQLx as SQLx Connection or Transaction
    participant PostgreSQL

    User->>Auth: Authenticated request
    Auth->>Tenant: User claims
    Tenant->>PostgreSQL: Verify active organization and membership
    PostgreSQL-->>Tenant: Tenant context or rejection
    Tenant->>Handler: organization_id and user_id

    alt Tenant transaction
        Handler->>SQLx: Begin transaction
        SQLx->>PostgreSQL: SET LOCAL zinhar.organization_id
        SQLx->>PostgreSQL: SET LOCAL zinhar.user_id
        SQLx->>PostgreSQL: SET LOCAL zinhar.rls_bypass = false
        Handler->>PostgreSQL: Query with explicit tenant predicates
        PostgreSQL->>PostgreSQL: Apply forced RLS policy
        PostgreSQL-->>Handler: Tenant-filtered result
        Handler->>SQLx: Commit or rollback
    else Privileged bypass transaction
        Handler->>SQLx: Begin narrowly authorized bypass
        SQLx->>PostgreSQL: SET LOCAL zinhar.rls_bypass = true
        PostgreSQL-->>Handler: Global or administrative result
        Handler->>SQLx: Commit or rollback
    end

    Note over SQLx,PostgreSQL: Session-level tenant connections use close_on_drop to avoid pooled context reuse
    Note over Handler,PostgreSQL: Same-tenant parent-child coherence requires dedicated tests (TIV-01 and CCU-01)
